52 PUNISHMENT PUNISHMENTS~
.                       {R=== PUNISHMENTS ==={x

Punishment is to be delivered at the descretion of the god doing the
punishing.  However, this list of punishments should be adhered to
for the most part.  Do not be excessive (one slay should drive the
point home, not multiple slays).  Accomplices are just as guilty as
the ones breaking the rules.  They should be treated the same way.
The Realm of the Dead (1212) is a favorite spot for interrogation and
dealing out punishment. For every punishment or watch needed to be 
kept, write a penalty (another kind of note).  Always explain clearly
why the person is being punished; make sure they understand.

1. Multicharring: Deny all characters involved in the multichar.

2. Cheating: First time, slay, purge equipment. After that, deny.

3. Bad language: Smite. Excessive badmouthing, deny.

4. Insulting the Gods: Roleplay this. Start with a warning of some
   kind, but if the insults continue, do what would be done by the
   god being insulted.

5. Bad roleplaying: First time, explain why it is bad roleplaying.
   Persistant bad roleplaying, smite. More, slay. More, deny. Use
   your judgement on the level of punishment to fit the infraction.

6. Multikilling: Slay, purge equipment. More than once, deny.

7. Spamming: Freeze, give the player warning. Persistant spamming,
   deny.

8. Storage chars: Slay, purge, deny.

9. Quitting out to avoid PK, etc: Slay, purge equipment. More such
   occurances, deny.

10. An Immortal breaks a rule: Inform an Implementor. If the Immortal
   is doing something devastating to the MUD without halt, freeze. Do
   whatever it takes to stop them. Make sure an Imp is informed.
~

